The Nigeria Labour Congress NLC , Cross River State branch has charged Governor Ben Ayade of Cross River State to expedite action on the implementation of N30,000 new minimum wage approved by the federal government so that its members can also  enjoy the minimum wage like their  counterparts in other states Chairman of the Nigeria Labour Congress in the state, Comrade Ben Ukpepi, gave the charge when he led a delegation of the NLC executives on a  courtesy visit to the office of the head of service, Mr. Christian Itah. He said it was pertinent for the state government to commence payment of the new minimum wage so that they can be happy like their colleagues in other states of the federation. Ukpepi stated that it has become worrisome for workers in the state to be denied their rights to enjoy the new  minimum wage that got approval by the federal government since April 2019,and warned that the union would be left with no other option than to call out its members to down their tools, should the state government fail to do the needful. The NLC helmsman, said,” We were happy when we just heard that state government had just given approval for a committee which awaits inauguration so that that committee  will handle all issues regarding to minimum wage. “Our humble appeal is that you expedite every action so that our members can begin to enjoy new minimum wage like their counterparts in other states of the federation. In his remarks, the Cross River State head of service, Mr. Chris Itah, stated that he would do  everything within his reach to ensure that the Service under his watch wouldn’t witness any form of industrial disharmony, stressing that there was a committee headed by the state deputy governor,  Prof. Ivara Esu, to get all matters related to a hitch – free service resolved.